properties.name: Fortynine Palms Trail
properties.description: There is a 300 foot (91 m) elevation gain in both directions, as you hike up and over a ridge dotted with barrel cactus. Beyond the ridge, descend to a fan palm oasis in a rocky canyon. Avoid this trail when it's hot out.
properties.opening_hours: open; Jul-Aug off "to allow bighorn sheep undisturbed access to surface water"

properties.name: Oasis of Mara Trail
properties.description: Provides an easy opportunity to visit a desert oasis and the increased chance to see desert wildlife with the rare water source that the oasis provides.

properties.description: The Pinto Mountains Zone is a rugged zone in the central part of the park. There are no roads or hiking trails. Backpackers entering this area should be well versed in off-trail travel and navigation.
